We write  
\( \displaystyle \sqrt{x-x^2}=\sqrt{x}\,\sqrt{1-x} \)  
and replace  
\(\sqrt{1-x}\approx1-\tfrac x2-\tfrac{x^2}{8}-\tfrac{x^3}{16}-\tfrac{5x^4}{2128}-\tfrac{7x^5}{256}\).  
Hence the integrand becomes  
\[
\sqrt{x-x^2}\;\approx\;x^{1/2}
-\tfrac12\,x^{3/2}
-\tfrac18\,x^{5/2}
-\tfrac1{16}\,x^{7/2}
-\tfrac5{2128}\,x^{9/2}
-\tfrac7{256}\,x^{11/2}\,,
\]  
and term‐by‐term integration from \(0\) to \(1/4\) gives  

\[
\int_0^{1/4}\sqrt{x-x^2}\,dx
\;\approx\;
\Bigl[\;
\frac{x^{3/2}}{3/2}
-\frac12\frac{x^{5/2}}{5/2}
-\frac18\frac{x^{7/2}}{7/2}
-\frac1{16}\frac{x^{9/2}}{9/2}
-\frac5{2128}\frac{x^{11/2}}{11/2}
-\frac7{256}\frac{x^{13/2}}{13/2}
\Bigr]_{0}^{1/4}.
\]  

Evaluating at \(x=1/4\) (and noting \((1/4)^{m+1/2}=1/4^{m}\cdot1/2\)) one finds

\[
\int_0^{1/4}\sqrt{x-x^2}\,dx
\approx
\frac1{12}
-\frac1{160}
-\frac1{3584}
-\frac1{36864}
-\frac{1}{4.8\times10^6}
-\frac{1}{1.9\times10^6}
\approx0.07678.
\]

Numerically,
\[
\int_{0}^{1/4}\sqrt{x-x^2}\,dx\approx7.678\times10^{-2}.
\]
